The paper proposes a network architecture for action recognition that integrates visual cues such as pose, motion, and raw images. This involves computer vision techniques such as image processing, deep learning, and machine learning, which are typically covered in the computer vision (cs.CV), machine learning (cs.LG), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also discusses spatio-temporal action localization, which involves tracking and localization techniques that are typically covered in the multimedia (cs.MM) and robotics (cs.RO) sub-categories.
